Fixed DB lock on worker_status and worker_runs INSERT by adding retry-with-backoff logic:

1. Updated app/orchestrator/worker_manager.py `_update_worker_status()` method with 5 retry attempts, 0.5s exponential backoff (0, 0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0s)
2. Verified app/orchestrator/worker.py already has proper retry logic (5 attempts with exponential backoff) for both:
   - `_update_worker_status()` method (handles worker_status UPDATE)
   - Stub INSERT in `spawn_worker()` method (handles worker_runs INSERT)
3. Verified app/orchestrator/agent_tracker.py already has retry logic on all update methods
4. Verified database config has WAL mode enabled and busy_timeout set (main: 10000ms, independent: 15000ms)

Added comprehensive test suite with 6 tests covering:
- Success on first attempt
- Retries on lock + eventual success
- Gives up gracefully after 5 attempts
- Inactive status updates
- Creates new records if missing
- Exponential backoff delays

All new tests passing (6/6). Verified existing worker-related tests still pass.
